-- Brookfield gets court OK to buy Atlantic City's Revel casino
-- By Tom Hals in Wilmington
-- Tue Oct 07, 2014 01:00PM EDT
-- None



Oct 7 (Reuters) - An affiliate of Brookfield Asset Management <BAMa.TO> on Tuesday got court approval to buy Atlantic City, New Jersey's shuttered Revel Casino Hotel for $110 million in cash after a judge rejected complaints the auction for the bankrupt complex was tainted.

